    <div class="container content">
      <!-- modify if necessary (move visualizations in separate pages) -->
      <h2 id="viz1">Visualization 1</h2>

      
	  
      <img src= "https://github.com/CLOTAIL/Neoma_Course/blob/master/Evolution%20march%C3%A9s.png?raw=true"
	  
	  
	  </img>
	  
	  <h3>Interpretation 1</h3>

      <p>
       In the visualization 1 we can see the evolution of the USA and European stock index equities after the 2007 Financial Market Crisis.
	   In this case we can notify that the financial Markets took more than 10 years to rebound after the Financial Crisis.
	   The Index stocks are the nasdaq( the technologic US Market), Dow Jones (The famouse US stock index),
	   Cac 40 (The 40th best stocks capitalisation in France),
	   Dax(The German Index), FTSE( The English index).
	   We can also notify that the different financial markets has shared the same tendance. For exemple in 2017 the markets has grow significantly ,
	   We can suppose that there is a correlation between the US and European Finance Markets.
	   We will analyze this hypothesis in the visualization 2.
      </p>

	  
      <h2 id="viz1">Visualization 2</h2>

      
	  
      <img src= "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CLOTAIL/Neoma_Course/master/corr.png"
	  
	  
	  </img>

      <h3>Interpretation 2</h3>
		In this case We can see the correlation between the differents index and there is the Amazon stock too.
		We can see obeviously that the US Index are not significantly correlated but they reacted in an opposite moves in the same time.
		I think we need to test this hypothesis with index which most similar (in the contruction of the index) as possible.
		The Amazon stock is highly correlated to the Nasdaq ( his own market) and the Dow Jones.
		The European Index are highly correlated between them. The FTSE moves a just a little different than the other but in generally in the same way.
      <p>
        
      </p>

      <h3>Discussion </h3>
		
		The difficulties of this project: 
		<ul>
		
		<li>To take the good informations that you need to show.</li>
		<li>Traiting the Data : use the good packages</li>
		<li>Order the Data for example compare an asset with an index is problematic</li>
		<li>Merge different Data : find the good axis and be sure you have the same common dates for examples(for having a long historical dataset)</li>
		<li>Plot the Data : my biggest problematic i spent more than 3 days to try to plot how i want my data.
			I decided to show the most importants informations i wanted to share.</li>
		
		
		
		</ul>
		
		
		
      <p>
      
      </p>

      <h3>Sources</h3>

      <p>
        For this project i had downloaded the dataset from <a href= "https://fr.investing.com/indices/nasdaq-composite-historical-data."> Investing.com </a>
		I used some simple code and the must knowed packages like Pandas , CSV and Matplolib.
      </p>
